  "prompt": "Which method of abortion is more likely to cause vomiting?",
  "response": "There are generally two common methods of abortion: medication abortion and surgical abortion. \n\n1. **Medication Abortion:**\n   - This method involves taking medications, typically mifepristone followed by misoprostol. Misoprostol, in particular, is known to cause gastrointestinal side effects, including nausea and vomiting. Therefore, medication abortion is more commonly associated with vomiting compared to surgical abortion.\n\n2. **Surgical Abortion:**\n   - Surgical methods, such as aspiration (or suction dilation and curettage, D&C), are less likely to cause vomiting directly. However, some individuals may experience nausea and vomiting as a result of anesthesia or sedation used during the procedure.\n\nIf vomiting or any other severe side effects occur, it's important for individuals to contact their healthcare provider for guidance. Each person\u2019s experience can vary, and healthcare providers can offer advice on managing side effects.",
